        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 2:37PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 237 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
southeastern Colorado Springs, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Southeastern Colorado Springs, Fountain, Schriever Space Force Base,
Security, Security-Widefield, and Fort Carson.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
